<br>
It's been a long time since I have graced the lands of RK.  Between my own game development project (any coders or modelers out there?) and Dark Age Of Camelot, I had simply allowed my subscription to expire and uninstalled AO.  Recently, a friend mentioned how much the game had been improved.  I was skeptical, of course, given Funcom's treatment of our profession in the past.  <br>
<br>
Getting bored with DAoC is relatively easy (complete lack of depth, but not bad for kids), so I bit the bullet and went through the quick process of reinstalling AO and the UNBELIEVABLY LONG process of auto-updating it.  Once back the game world, I was literally shocked into remembering the beauty of the graphics (compared in this case to DAoC and EQ) and the richness of the surroundings.  <br>
<br>
On a humorous note, after being completely used to using DAoC's chat commands, I couldn't remember how to A)send a message to just one person B)send a message to just my group and C)  UPLOAD A MISSION MAP :)<br>
<br>
But I figured it out/remembered it.<br>
<br>
AND LO AND BEHOLD, DESPITE ALL THE BITCHING ABOUT KICKS...MY CHARACTER THREW A HIGH KICK AGAINST THE VERY FIRST MOB I ATTACKED AFTER REACHING 3RD LEVEL.<br>
<br>
One question...what is this over-equipping thing?  And have they basically fixed our weapon use?  Do I still have to make sure I unequip all weapons before zoning?<br>
<br>
If the weapons are fixed...what are most of you doing?  Single or dual?<br>
<br>
Welcome me home...I'm back and I'm having a blast :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uiccusion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iccusion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#660000>(4/5/02 4:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1856.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I haven't played in six months...happily suprised.</span><hr size=1> You threw a kick?  At 3rd level?<br>
