<br>
I've often thought that the secret of kicking may lie in the sequence of buttons pushed.  For instance, I'm not sure about everyone else, but I do this;<br>
<br>
1) Target and approach target, getting within melee range.<br>
2) Hit Q to initiate attack<br>
3) Wait for the first hit to land then quickly hit BRAWL and Attack of the Snake.<br>
<br>
However...I wonder if kicking might have something to do with timing in these attacks.  Like an unseen counter that calculates how long you went between pushing brawl before the next automatic punch landed...something along those lines.  It would be completely invisible to the player.<br>
<br>
